		    <title class="- topic/title ">
			      <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">22.103-1</ph> Definition.</title>
		    <conbody class="- topic/body concept/conbody ">
			      <p class="- topic/p ">“Normal workweek,” as used in this subpart, means, generally, a workweek of 40 hours. Outside the United States and its outlying areas, a workweek longer than 40 hours is considered normal if-</p>
			      <ol id="d1271e16" class="- topic/ol ">
				        <li class="- topic/li ">
					          <ol id="d1271e20" class="- topic/ol ">
						            <li class="- topic/li ">
							              <p id="d1285e24" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph>
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
								                The workweek does not exceed the norm for the area, as determined by local custom, tradition, or law; and</p>
						            </li>
						            <li class="- topic/li ">
							              <p id="d1285e33" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph>
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
								                The hours worked in excess of 40 in the workweek are not compensated at a premium rate of pay.</p>
						            </li>
					          </ol>
				        </li>
			      </ol>
		    </conbody>
